<li><a href="http://www.moq.org/" class="external text" title="http://www.moq.org/" rel="nofollow">MOQ.org</a>, a forum for the discussion of Robert M Pirsig's Metaphysics of Quality</li>
<li><a href="http://www.robertpirsig.org" class="external text" title="http://www.robertpirsig.org" rel="nofollow">robertpirsig.org</a>, A website containing a number of papers concerned with the Metaphysics of Quality.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.synaptic.bc.ca/ejournal/Robert_M_Pirsig.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.synaptic.bc.ca/ejournal/Robert_M_Pirsig.htm" rel="nofollow">Robert M. Pirsig &amp; Quality</a></li>
<li><a href="http://ww2.usca.edu/ResearchProjects/ProfessorGurr/gallery/view_album.php?set_albumName=Pictures-Robert-Pirsigs-original-1968-trip" class="external text" title="http://ww2.usca.edu/ResearchProjects/ProfessorGurr/gallery/view_album.php?set_albumName=Pictures-Robert-Pirsigs-original-1968-trip" rel="nofollow">Pictures taken by Pirsig</a> from the trip made famous in his book</li>
<li><a href="http://www.bartneck.de/projects/research/pirsig/index.html" class="external text" title="http://www.bartneck.de/projects/research/pirsig/index.html" rel="nofollow">Aerial View</a> of Pirsig's route, including texts, audio and books.</li>
<li><a href="http://zamm.home.att.net/" class="external text" title="http://zamm.home.att.net/" rel="nofollow">ZAMM Travel Route</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=4612364" class="external text" title="http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=4612364" rel="nofollow">Audio: 1974 NPR Interview with Pirsig</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=4612367" class="external text" title="http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=4612367" rel="nofollow">Audio: 1992 NPR Interview with Pirsig</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.philosophersnet.com/magazine/pirsig_transcript.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.philosophersnet.com/magazine/pirsig_transcript.htm" rel="nofollow">Interview from 2005 regarding MoQ</a></li>
<li><a href="http://observer.guardian.co.uk/review/story/0,,1951397,00.html" class="external text" title="http://observer.guardian.co.uk/review/story/0,,1951397,00.html" rel="nofollow">Guardian interview from 2006 Short version</a> and <a href="http://observer.guardian.co.uk/review/story/0,,1952011,00.html" class="external text" title="http://observer.guardian.co.uk/review/story/0,,1952011,00.html" rel="nofollow">Long version.</a></li>
<li><a href="http://sites.google.com/site/foragain/Home/zen-and-the-art-of-motorcycle-maintenance-an-unappreciation" class="external text" title="http://sites.google.com/site/foragain/Home/zen-and-the-art-of-motorcycle-maintenance-an-unappreciation" rel="nofollow"><i>Zen and the Art of Motorcycle Maintenance, An Unappreciation</i></a>, an essay critical of the book's idea of value and its attempt to synthesise Eastern with Western philosophy.</li>
<li><a href="http://butler-bowdon.com/zen-and-the-art-of-motorcycle-maintenance.html" class="external text" title="http://butler-bowdon.com/zen-and-the-art-of-motorcycle-maintenance.html" rel="nofollow">Short essay</a> positing <i>Zen and the Art of Motorcycle Maintenance</i> as a modern spiritual classic.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=4612364" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=4612364" rel="nofollow">[1]</a> 1974 NPR interview with Pirsig</li>
</ul>


